Source: xmlrcs
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Petr Bena <petr@localhost>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
 cmake,
 dh-python,
 g++,
 pkgconf,
 python3-all
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://wikitech.wikimedia.org/wiki/XmlRcs

Package: xmlrcsd
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, redis-server
Description: XML recent changes TCP server daemon
 xmlrcsd serves the XMLRCS recent changes stream to TCP clients.
 It consumes XML items from Redis and exposes them on port 8822.

Package: es2r
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, python3, python3-redis, python3-requests, python3-sseclient, redis-server
Description: EventStreams to Redis feeder for XMLRCS
 es2r connects to Wikimedia EventStreams, converts recent changes to XML,
 and pushes them into Redis for consumption by xmlrcsd.
